{"updated_at": "2011-06-25T13:12:30Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-06-25T13:12:10Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1437790", "id": 1437790, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1857", "issue_id": 1857, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/vijaydev", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "91160e88d86db6328f3e81313ae500c6", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/91160e88d86db6328f3e81313ae500c6?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff3e3ac334dea11f7cc8a25c6b7500d80.png", "id": 146214, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/events{/privacy}", "login": "vijaydev", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vijaydev/followers"}, "body": "Thinking about my approach, we could even remove the class_eval that creates all the methods that are recordable and let method_missing handle the recording completely. \r\n\r\nOr add change_table and any other missing methods to the class_eval code so that they are all recorded. In that case, if the method_missing is changed back to its original version, I'm not sure about the scenarios in which CommandRecorder should delegate to the database connection.\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "52384d18bd3543c151011483"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1857#issuecomment-1437790"}
